    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7bb7709e"
      },
      "source": [
        "As you can see, the values in `lw` are numeric strings, but they do not contain the `+` operator. Therefore, the `adding_str` function skipped these columns.\n",
        "\n",
        "To convert these remaining object columns to integers, we can explicitly apply `pd.to_numeric` to them."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7b30f025",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "6eead872-9b82-4305-a231-23297b9bc24d"
      },
      "source": [
        "cols_to_convert = ['lw', 'lf', 'cf', 'rf', 'rw']\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in cols_to_convert:\n",
        "    # Convert to numeric, coercing errors to NaN, then fill NaN with 0 and convert to int\n",
        "    df_cleaned[col] = pd.to_numeric(df_cleaned[col], errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Verify the dtypes after conversion\n",
        "df_cleaned[cols_to_convert].info()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
